# ESP32-Hub

BLE scanner and WiFi bridge. Scans for nRF52840 BLE advertisements, aggregates sensor state, and relays to BeagleBone via UART and optionally to AWS via TCP.

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `main.c` | Application entry point |
| `ble_manager.c` | BLE stack init and coordination |
| `ble_scan.c` | BLE advertisement scanning |
| `ble_gattc.c` | BLE GATT client |
| `ble_light.c` | Smart light BLE handler |
| `ble_lock.c` | Smart lock BLE handler |
| `wifi_manager.c` | WiFi connection management |
| `uart_manager.c` | UART relay to BeagleBone |
| `tcp_manager.c` | TCP client |
| `aws_manager.c` | AWS IoT integration |
| `vroom_bus.c` | Internal message bus |
| `crash_log.c` | NVS-backed crash logging |
| `network_config.h` | Network configuration |
| `wifi_secrets.h` | WiFi credentials (not committed) |

## Build

```bash
cd esp32-hub
. $HOME/esp/esp-idf/export.sh

# Clean (avoid cache issues)
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub \
  -B ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub/build \
  fullclean

# Build
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub \
  -B ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub/build \
  build
```

## Flash

```bash
idf.py -C ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub \
  -B ~/embedded-iot-hub/esp32-hub/build \
  -p /dev/ttyUSB1 flash
```

## Monitor

```bash
minicom -D /dev/ttyUSB1 -b 115200
```

## Crash Logging

`CRASH_HALT` controls panic handler behavior:
- `0` — log PC to NVS and restart (default, release/battery)
- `1` — halt forever for JTAG debugger

The flag is set at build time via CMake and does not require modifying source.
